Heat the @Tomato Basil Soup{1000%milliliter} per packet instructions.

Meanwhile, gently flatten the @Brioche Buns{2} with your hands.

Spread @Mayo{2%sachet} over the cut side of each bun base.

Sprinkle the @Grated Cheese{50%grams} on top.

Spread the @Ballymaloe Tomato Relish{1%pot} over the cut side of the bun lid and pop on top of the cheese.

Place a #large pan{} over medium heat with a light drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the toastie and cover with a #lid{}.

Allow the buns to toast and the cheese to melt, pressing down occasionally with a #spatula{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}, ~{3-5%minutes} each side.

Halve the toasties and plate up.

Serve the warm soup alongside.

> An easy cheesy lunch featuring a melted cheese toastie with Ballymaloe relish and a creamy bowl of tomato basil soup.